description: SpaceX is targeting Wednesday, April 7 for launch of 60 Starlink satellites from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida. The instantaneous window is at 12:34 p.m. EDT, or 16:34 UTC, and a backup opportunity is available on Thursday, April 8 at 12:12 p.m. EDT, or 16:12 UTC.The Falcon 9 first stage rocket booster supporting this mission previously supported launch of NASA astronauts Bob Behnken and Doug Hurley to the International Space Station, ANASIS-II, CRS-21, Transporter-1, and two Starlink missions. Following stage separation, SpaceX will land Falcon 9‚Äôs first stage on the ‚ÄúOf Course I Still Love You‚Äù droneship, which will be located in the Atlantic Ocean. tags: [none]
description: Kelly Oubre Jr. knocked down two free throws with 7.7 seconds remaining in regulation to close out a 16-5 run and lift the Warriors over the Bucks, 122-121. The Warriors improve to 24-27 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 32-18.
